{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/ironcev/awesome-roslyn/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"ironcev/awesome-roslyn","descriptionHTML":"<div>Curated list of awesome Roslyn books, tutorials, open-source projects, analyzers, code fixes, refactorings, and source generators</div>","description":"Curated list of awesome Roslyn books, tutorials, open-source projects, analyzers, code fixes, refactorings, and source generators","stargazerCount":421,"repoUpdatedTime":1615322591000},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-30T23:08:12.394Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/tom-englert/Nullable.Extended\">Nullable.Extended</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/tom-englert/Nullable.Extended\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5,\"repo\":\"tom-englert/Nullable.Extended\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Roslyn tools and analyzers to improve the experience when coding with nullable reference types.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-09T20:43:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/diegofrata/Generator.Equals\">Generator.Equals</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/diegofrata/Generator.Equals\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">17</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":17,\"repo\":\"diegofrata/Generator.Equals\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Automatically implements equality and hashing for classes and records. Supports different comparison strategies. Offers similar functionality like IL weaving-based <a href=\"https://github.com/Fody/Equals\">Equals.Fody</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Fody/Equals\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">107</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":107,\"repo\":\"Fody/Equals\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-19T19:15:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blog Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/microsoft-open-source-stories/how-microsoft-rewrote-its-c-compiler-in-c-and-made-it-open-source-4ebed5646f98\">How Microsoft rewrote its C# compiler in C# and made it open source</a> - Roslyn's journey, presented by Mads Torgersen, the lead designer of C#. Inspiring story on how Roslyn project started and why, and what it took to make it open source.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-30T16:26:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cezarypiatek/MappingGenerator\">Mapping Generator</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cezarypiatek/MappingGenerator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">883</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":883,\"repo\":\"cezarypiatek/MappingGenerator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Code fix that generates arbitrary complex object-object mappings. It recognizes out of the box a large number of scenarios where mappings are used. A design-time alternative to <a href=\"https://automapper.org/\">AutoMapper</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-21T18:17:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/martinothamar/WrapperValueObject\">WrapperValueObject</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/martinothamar/WrapperValueObject\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">29</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":29,\"repo\":\"martinothamar/WrapperValueObject\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Creates boilerplate free wrappers around types. Especially useful for creating <a href=\"https://andrewlock.net/series/using-strongly-typed-entity-ids-to-avoid-primitive-obsession/\">strongly typed wrappers around primitive types</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-21T06:05:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/introducing-c-source-generators/\">Introducing C# Source Generators</a> - Original announcement of the C# 9.0 Source Generators feature. Explains what source generators are, in which scenarios they are useful, and shows how to write a simple source generator.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/new-c-source-generator-samples/\">New C# Source Generator Samples</a> - Samples on how to write a non-trivial code generator driven by additional, non-code files like CSV files or <a href=\"https://mustache.github.io/\">Mustache</a> templates.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/amis92/csharp-source-generators\">C# Source Generators</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/amis92/csharp-source-generators\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">258</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":258,\"repo\":\"amis92/csharp-source-generators\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Comprehensive list of additional learning sources, samples, and experimental and productive source generators. A perfect reference once you grasp the basics.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lsoft/DpdtInject\">DpDtInject</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lsoft/DpdtInject\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12,\"repo\":\"lsoft/DpdtInject\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Proof-of-concept of a dependency injection container that transfers huge piece of resolving logic to the compilation stage. Offers additional compile-time safety and fast runtime resolution.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trampster/JsonSrcGen\">JsonSrcGen</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/trampster/JsonSrcGen\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">76</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":76,\"repo\":\"trampster/JsonSrcGen\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Reflection-free JSON serializer. Allows extremely fast JSON processing by generating reflection-free serializers at the compile time.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sourcegen.dev/\">Source Generator Playground</a> - Online application that lets you experiment with source generators. Perfect for learning and testing your ideas. Write your own source generator or learn from built-in examples and see the generated output.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/YairHalberstadt/stronginject\">StrongInject</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/YairHalberstadt/stronginject\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">391</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":391,\"repo\":\"YairHalberstadt/stronginject\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Compile-time dependency injection container. Compile-time checked, reflection-free and runtime code generation free, thus fast and <a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/app-trimming-in-net-5/\">app-trimming</a>-friendly.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RudolfKurka/StructPacker\">StructPacker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/RudolfKurka/StructPacker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">18</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":18,\"repo\":\"RudolfKurka/StructPacker\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Low-level, lightweight and performance-focused serializer for C# struct types. Auto-generates C# serialization code to achieve peak runtime performance and efficiency.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Source Generators</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wieslawsoltes/SourceGenerators\">Svg to C# Source Generators</a> - SVG to C# compiler. Compiles SVG drawing markup to C# using <a href=\"https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp\">SkiaSharp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2164,\"repo\":\"mono/SkiaSharp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> as rendering engine.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-16T17:06:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn/blob/master/docs/wiki/How-To-Write-a-C%23-Analyzer-and-Code-Fix.md\">How To Write a C# Analyzer and Code Fix</a> - The mother of all Roslyn tutorials :-) A realistic step-by-step introduction to syntax and semantic analysis as well as the syntax transformation.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-09T19:05:04.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SergeyTeplyakov/ErrorProne.NET\">ErrorProne.NET</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/SergeyTeplyakov/ErrorProne.NET\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">545</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":545,\"repo\":\"SergeyTeplyakov/ErrorProne.NET\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Set of analyzers and code fixes focusing on the correctness and performance of C# programs. Inspired with Google's <a href=\"https://github.com/google/error-prone\">Error Prone</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/google/error-prone\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5572,\"repo\":\"google/error-prone\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-13T08:18:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Frameworks for Testing Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-sdk/tree/master/src/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Testing\">Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Testing</a> - Library for testing analyzers and code fixes with NUnit, xUnit and MSTest frameworks. A part of <a href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-sdk\">Roslyn SDK</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-sdk\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">277</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":277,\"repo\":\"dotnet/roslyn-sdk\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-11-13T08:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Frameworks for Testing Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cezarypiatek/RoslynTestKit\">RoslynTestKit</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cezarypiatek/RoslynTestKit\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"cezarypiatek/RoslynTestKit\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Lightweight framework for writing unit tests for analyzers, code fixes, refactorings, and completion providers. It's unit testing framework agnostic.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-11-13T08:34:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dotnetcore/FlubuCore\">FlubuCore</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dotnetcore/FlubuCore\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">715</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":715,\"repo\":\"dotnetcore/FlubuCore\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Cross platform build automation tool for building projects and executing deployment scripts using C# code.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-24T09:39:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.syncfusion.com/ebooks/roslyn\">Roslyn Succinctly</a> - <em>Free e-book</em> by Alessandro Del Sole and the perfect book to start with. Explains Roslyn APIs and afterward focuses on writing analyzers and refactorings.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-03-01T21:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.apress.com/la/book/9781484221105\">.NET Development Using the Compiler API</a> - Book by Jason Bock. Besides analyzers and refactorings, it also explains the scripting API and provides an interesting reflection on the future of the Compiler API.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-03-01T21:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/application-development/roslyn-cookbook\">Roslyn Cookbook</a> - Book by Manish Vasani, a member of the Roslyn analyzers team. After covering analyzers, refactorings, and scripting in detail, the book goes in-depth explaining how to develop new C# language features and contribute to the Roslyn source code.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-03-01T21:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/DotNetAnalyzers\">.NET Analyzers</a> - GitHub organization for the development of Roslyn analyzers. Various repositories within the organization cover analyzers for ASP.NET Core, WPF, IDisposable, usages of System.Reflection, etc.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-24T13:50:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://joshvarty.com/learn-roslyn-now/\">Learn Roslyn Now</a> - Series of blog posts that explore the Roslyn compiler API. It introduces the power of Roslyn through small self-contained examples. A perfect tutorial to start with :-)</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/dn879356.aspx\">C# and Visual Basic - Use Roslyn to Write a Live Code Analyzer for Your API</a> - Older but still not outdated, very detailed MSDN article on writing code analyzers.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/dn904670.aspx\">C# - Adding a Code Fix to Your Roslyn Analyzer</a> - The sequel to the previous MSDN article. A detailed introduction into code fixes.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bridgedotnet/Bridge\">Bridge</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bridgedotnet/Bridge\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2221,\"repo\":\"bridgedotnet/Bridge\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - C# to JavaScript transpiler. Write modern mobile and web apps in C# and run them anywhere in JavaScript.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/icsharpcode/CodeConverter/\">Code Converter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/icsharpcode/CodeConverter/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">463</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":463,\"repo\":\"icsharpcode/CodeConverter\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - C# to VB.NET and VB.NET to C# transpiler.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pvginkel/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.PatternMatching\">CodeAnalysis.CSharp.PatternMatching</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pvginkel/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.PatternMatching\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">18</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":18,\"repo\":\"pvginkel/Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.PatternMatching\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Intuitive pattern matching for Roslyn syntax trees. Simplifies C# syntax and semantic analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/AArnott/CodeGeneration.Roslyn\">CodeGeneration.Roslyn</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/AArnott/CodeGeneration.Roslyn\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">402</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":402,\"repo\":\"AArnott/CodeGeneration.Roslyn\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Roslyn-based Code Generation during a build with design-time support.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/filipw/dotnet-script\">dotnet-script</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/filipw/dotnet-script\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.7k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1685,\"repo\":\"filipw/dotnet-script\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Runs C# scripts from the .NET CLI, defines NuGet packages inline and edit/debugs them in VS Code.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ashmind/mirrorsharp\">MirrorSharp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ashmind/mirrorsharp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">110</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":110,\"repo\":\"ashmind/mirrorsharp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Online C#, VB.NET, and F# code editor. Features code completion, method signature help, quick fixes, and diagnostics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://roslynpad.net/\">RoslynPad</a> - Cross-platform C# editor. Features code completion, method signature help, quick fixes, and diagnostics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/KirillOsenkov/RoslynQuoter\">RoslynQuoter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/KirillOsenkov/RoslynQuoter\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">575</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":575,\"repo\":\"KirillOsenkov/RoslynQuoter\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Online tool that for a given C# program generates syntax tree API calls that construct syntax tree of that program.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://scriptcs.net/\">scriptcs</a> - Turns C# into a powerful scripting tool. Features C# REPL, installation of NuGet packages, and execution of scripts with a single line of code.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/daveaglick/Scripty\">Scripty</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://git