g, and compiling C# code. Provides methods and helpers to generate classes, methods, statements, and expressions.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nventive/Uno.SourceGeneration\">Uno SourceGenerator</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nventive/Uno.SourceGeneration\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">102</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":102,\"repo\":\"nventive/Uno.SourceGeneration\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - C# source code generator based on a project being built, using all of its syntactic and semantic model information.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/code-cracker/code-cracker\">Code Cracker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/code-cracker/code-cracker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1051,\"repo\":\"code-cracker/code-cracker\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Analyzer library for C# and VB.NET. Offers diagnostics in many categories like performance, coding styles, as well as some basic refactorings.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/RoslynClrHeapAllocationAnalyzer\">Roslyn Clr Heap Allocation Analyzer</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/RoslynClrHeapAllocationAnalyzer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">511</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":511,\"repo\":\"Microsoft/RoslynClrHeapAllocationAnalyzer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - C# heap allocation analyzer that can detect explicit and many implicit allocations like boxing, closures, implicit delegate creations, etc.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/JosefPihrt/Roslynator\">Roslynator</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JosefPihrt/Roslynator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2041,\"repo\":\"JosefPihrt/Roslynator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Collection of 190+ analyzers and 190+ refactorings for C#. Covers coding style, code readability and simplification, removing redundancies, fixing compiler errors, and many more.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SonarSource/sonar-csharp\">SonarC#</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/SonarSource/sonar-csharp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">469</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":469,\"repo\":\"SonarSource/sonar-csharp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Static code analyzer for C# language used as an extension for the SonarQube platform.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/DotNetAnalyzers/StyleCopAnalyzers\">StyleCop Analyzers for the .NET Compiler Platform</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/DotNetAnalyzers/StyleCopAnalyzers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1841,\"repo\":\"DotNetAnalyzers/StyleCopAnalyzers\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Port of StyleCop rules to Roslyn.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Vannevelj/VSDiagnostics\">VSDiagnostics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Vannevelj/VSDiagnostics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">65</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":65,\"repo\":\"Vannevelj/VSDiagnostics\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Collection of code-quality analyzers. Covers usages of async methods, flags enums, best practices in exception handling as well as many other code-quality checks.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blog Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://robinsedlaczek.com/2015/04/29/inside-the-net-compiler-platform-performance-considerations-during-syntax-analysis-speakroslyn/\">Inside the .NET Compiler Platform – Performance Considerations during Syntax Analysis (#SpeakRoslyn)</a> - In-depth look at Roslyn's performance with the focus on memory consumption.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blog Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/ericlippert/2012/06/08/persistence-facades-and-roslyns-red-green-trees/\">Persistence, Facades and Roslyn's Red-Green Trees</a> - Inspiring introduction on how Roslyn team implemented immutable, reusable trees with cheap parent references and many other goodies. Quote: \"But on the Roslyn team we routinely do impossible things\" :-)</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blog Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.jetbrains.com/dotnet/2014/04/10/resharper-and-roslyn-qa/\">ReSharper and Roslyn: Q&#x26;A</a> - Excellent explanation why ReSharper will not use Roslyn. Includes good discussion on static code analysis and some limits of Roslyn.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blog Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/csharpfaq/2014/01/15/roslyn-performance-matt-gertz/\">Roslyn performance (Matt Gertz)</a> - Insight on how Roslyn team approaches the topic of evaluating and achieving performance.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nXljhGDokqA\">The Power of Roslyn</a> - Great talk by Kasey Uhlenhuth at NDC Oslo 2018 covering Roslyn essentials and APIs and tools for building code analyzers and fixes.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-18T22:35:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bkoelman/CSharpGuidelinesAnalyzer\">CSharpGuidelinesAnalyzer</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bkoelman/CSharpGuidelinesAnalyzer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">78</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":78,\"repo\":\"bkoelman/CSharpGuidelinesAnalyzer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Reports diagnostics for C# coding guidelines (<a href=\"https://csharpcodingguidelines.com/\">https://csharpcodingguidelines.com/</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-06-02T10:17:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/icsharpcode/RefactoringEssentials/\">Refactoring Essentials for Visual Studio</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/icsharpcode/RefactoringEssentials/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">639</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":639,\"repo\":\"icsharpcode/RefactoringEssentials\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Refactorings, analyzers and code fixes for C# and VB.NET.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T19:53:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Analyzers, Code Fixes, and Refactorings</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-analyzers\">.NET Compiler Platform (\"Roslyn\") Analyzers</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-analyzers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1033,\"repo\":\"dotnet/roslyn-analyzers\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Diagnostic analyzers developed by the Roslyn team. Initially developed to help flesh out the design and implementation of the static analysis APIs. The analyzers cover code quality, .NET Core, desktop .NET Framework, comments in code, and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T17:47:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sharplab.io/\">SharpLab</a> - .NET code playground. Displays intermediate steps and results of code compilation. Shows the code as compiler sees it. Allows selecting different branches and versions of Roslyn. Runs C#, VB.NET, and F# code in the browser.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T03:25:36.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.omnisharp.net/\">OmniSharp</a> - Enables a cross platform .NET development in the editor of your choice. A family of open source projects, each with one goal: To enable a great .NET experience in your editor of choice.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T03:23:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\">roslyn-linq-rewrite</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">684</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":684,\"repo\":\"antiufo/roslyn-linq-rewrite\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Compiles C# code by first rewriting the syntax trees of LINQ expressions using plain procedural code. This increases performance by minimizes heap allocations and dynamic dispatch.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-14T02:00:20.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core","repo":"thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/miguelmota/awesome-amazon-alexa","repo":"miguelmota/awesome-amazon-alexa"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"ironcev/awesome-roslyn","id":"awesomes/github.com/ironcev/awesome-roslyn","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/miguelmota/awesome-amazon-alexa"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}